AIQILE Bolivia――more than 80 people died and at least 100 were proved injured in the devastating 
earthquake last Friday, said Bolivia’s national Civil Defense Service director Luis Montero.
The earthquake, which measured 6.6 degree, hit this distant area of eastern Bolivia early Friday morning.
The small towns of Aiquile and Totora, some 620 kilometres and 645 kilometres east of La Paz 
separately had a bad effect. Both have been declared disaster areas.
Scores of people are missing, and as many as 15 000 were left homeless. At least 950 homes in 
the area have been damaged, and as many as 600 destroyed, Montero said. 
